{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781761417678,"sessionID":"ses_126bff004ffeidXJpk4781In70","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_Eo9lxj262lzA6BfvzKkITqUy","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/005-verification-and-remediation/006-deep-review-017-021-remediation/review-r2/scopes/A-search-retrieval/spec.md","offset":1,"limit":2000},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/005-verification-and-remediation/006-deep-review-017-021-remediation/review-r2/scopes/A-search-retrieval/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Audit Scope — Search & Retrieval Subsystem\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: Independent gpt-5.5 deep-review **audit** of the search/retrieval code of the system-spec-kit MCP server. This is a REVIEW-SCOPE target — there is NO new implementation to verify. Audit the shipped code below for real defects and report P0/P1/P2 findings with `file:line` evidence. Do not invent findings; a clean PASS is a valid outcome.\n5: \n6: ## Code under review\n7: All paths under `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/`:\n8: - `lib/search/pipeline/stage1-*.ts`, `lib/search/pipeline/stage2-fusion.ts` — candidate generation + post-fusion scoring signals\n9: - `lib/search/confidence-scoring.ts`, `lib/search/confidence-calibration.ts`, `lib/search/recovery-payload.ts` — result confidence, isotonic/PAV calibration, recovery payloads\n10: - `lib/search/trigger-embedding-backfill.ts` — trigger-phrase embedding backfill\n11: - BM25 field weights, hybrid search scope-then-limit, vector read-path resilience, retrieval gating & recall recovery (search/retrieval modules under `lib/search/` and `lib/`)\n12: - the search/query handlers under `handlers/` that call into `lib/search`\n13: \n14: ## Review dimensions\n15: correctness, security, performance, concurrency/cancellation, maintainability, and spec-vs-code drift. Emphasize numeric correctness (weight sums, calibration monotonicity, score normalization on the real 0..1 signal), cross-module seams, and any unbounded/synchronous work on the read path.\n16: \n17: ## Notes\n18: Round-1 already audited the 017-021 fixes (cancel-delay, calibration PAV pooling, cache mtime invalidation, confidence 3-factor weights). This round BROADENS to the whole search/retrieval surface — focus on code those fixes did not directly touch.\n\n(End of file - total 18 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Audit Scope — Search & Retrieval Subsystem\n\n## Purpose\nIndependent gpt-5.5 deep-review **audit** of the search/retrieval code of the system-spec-kit MCP server. This is a REVIEW-SCOPE target — there is NO new implementation to verify. Audit the shipped code below for real defects and report P0/P1/P2 findings with `file:line` evidence. Do not invent findings; a clean PASS is a valid outcome.\n\n## Code under review\nAll paths under `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/`:\n- `lib/search/pipeline/stage1-*.ts`, `lib/search/pipeline/stage2-fusion.ts` — candidate generation + post-fusion scoring signals\n- `lib/search/confidence-scoring.ts`, `lib/search/confidence-calibration.ts`, `lib/search/recovery-payload.ts` — result confidence, isotonic/PAV calibration, recovery payloads\n- `lib/search/trigger-embedding-backfill.ts` — trigger-phrase embedding backfill\n- BM25 field weights, hybrid search scope-then-limit, vector read-path resilience, retrieval gating & recall recovery (search/retrieval modules under `lib/search/` and `lib/`)\n- the search/query handlers under `handlers/` that call into `lib/search`\n\n## Review dimensions\ncorrectness, security, performance, concurrency/cancellation, maintainability, and spec-vs-code drift. Emphasize numeric correctness (weight sums, calibration monotonicity, score normalization on the real 0..1 signal), cross-module seams, and any unbounded/synchronous work on the read path.\n\n## Notes\nRound-1 already audited the 017-021 fixes (cancel-delay, calibration PAV pooling, cache mtime invalidation, confidence 3-factor weights). This round BROADENS to the whole search/retrieval surface — focus on code those fixes did not directly touch.","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/005-verification-and-remediation/006-deep-review-017-021-remediation/review-r2/scopes/A-search-retrieval/spec.md","text":"# Audit Scope — Search & Retrieval Subsystem\n\n## Purpose\nIndependent gpt-5.5 deep-review **audit** of the search/retrieval code of the system-spec-kit MCP server. This is a REVIEW-SCOPE target — there is NO new implementation to verify. Audit the shipped code below for real defects and report P0/P1/P2 findings with `file:line` evidence. Do not invent findings; a clean PASS is a valid outcome.\n\n## Code under review\nAll paths under `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/`:\n- `lib/search/pipeline/stage1-*.ts`, `lib/search/pipeline/stage2-fusion.ts` — candidate generation + post-fusion scoring signals\n- `lib/search/confidence-scoring.ts`, `lib/search/confidence-calibration.ts`, `lib/search/recovery-payload.ts` — result confidence, isotonic/PAV calibration, recovery payloads\n- `lib/search/trigger-embedding-backfill.ts` — trigger-phrase embedding backfill\n- BM25 field weights, hybrid search scope-then-limit, vector read-path resilience, retrieval gating & recall recovery (search/retrieval modules under `lib/search/` and `lib/`)\n- the search/query handlers under `handlers/` that call into `lib/search`\n\n## Review dimensions\ncorrectness, security, performance, concurrency/cancellation, maintainability, and spec-vs-code drift. Emphasize numeric correctness (weight sums, calibration monotonicity, score normalization on the real 0..1 signal), cross-module seams, and any unbounded/synchronous work on the read path.\n\n## Notes\nRound-1 already audited the 017-021 fixes (cancel-delay, calibration PAV pooling, cache mtime invalidation, confidence 3-factor weights). This round BROADENS to the whole search/retrieval surface — focus on code those fixes did not directly touch.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":18,"totalLines":18,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/005-verification-and-remediation/006-deep-review-017-021-remediation/review-r2/scopes/A-search-retrieval/spec.md","time":{"start":1781761417674,"end":1781761417678}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_03ee076253aab8e4016a33858926c0819194bf8f01afcfd4e2"}},"id":"prt_ed9419fc60018VGILqFDBc17CD","sessionID":"ses_126bff004ffeidXJpk4781In70","messageID":"msg_ed9418b1a00148hbnFudKhbUHt"}}
